{{Protestantism}} The following '''list of Protestant missionary societies''' is a list of [[Protestant]] [[Christian]] [[Mission (Christian)|missionary]] organizations that began between 1691-1900.<ref>Encyclopædia Britannica (1911)</ref>
==Missionary societies in the United Kingdom== * 1649 [[New England Company]] <ref>[http://www.newenglandcompany.org/htms/history.htm]</ref> * 1691 [[Christian Faith Society]] for the West Indies * 1698 [[Society for Promoting Christian Knowledge]] * 1701 [[Society for the Propagation of the Gospel in Foreign Parts]] * 1709 [[Society in Scotland for the Propagation of Christian Knowledge]] * 1732 [[Moravian Church|Moravian]] Missions * 1792 [[Baptist Missionary Society]] * 1795 [[London Missionary Society]] * 1796 [[Scottish United Presbyterian Mission|Scottish Missionary Society]] * 1799 [[Church Missionary Society]] * 1799 [[Religious Tract Society]] * 1804 [[British and Foreign Bible Society]] * 1809 London Society for Promoting Christianity Amongst the Jews (now known as the [[Church's Ministry Among Jewish People]] or CMJ) * 1813 [[English Wesleyan Mission|Wesleyan Missionary Society]] * 1817 General [[Baptist Missionary Society]] * 1823 [[Intercontinental Church Society|Colonial and Continental Church Society]] * 1825 [[Church of Scotland]] Mission Boards * 1825 [[Scottish Bible Society|National Bible Society of Scotland]] * 1831 [[Trinitarian Bible Society]] * 1832 [[Wesleyan Ladies' Auxiliary for Female Education in Foreign Countries]] * 1835 United Secession (afterwards United Presbyterian) Foreign Missions * 1836 [[Colonial Missionary Society]] a.k.a. [[Commonwealth Missionary Society]] * 1840 [[Irish Presbyterian Mission|Irish Presbyterian Missionary Society]] * 1840 Welsh [[Calvinistic Methodists|Calvinistic Methodist]] Missionary Society * 1841 [[Colonial Bishoprics Fund]] * 1841 [http://www.emms.org/ Edinburgh Medical Missionary Society] * 1843 [[British Society for the Propagation of the Gospel Among the Jews]] * 1843 [[Free Church of Scotland (1843-1900)|Free Church of Scotland]] Missions * 1843 [[Primitive Methodist]] African and Colonial Missions * 1843 [[Methodist New Connexion]] in England Foreign Missions * 1844 [[South American Missionary Society]] * 1847 [[English Presbyterian Mission|Presbyterian Church in England Foreign Missions]] * 1858 [[Christian Vernacular Education Society for India]] * 1860 [[Central African Mission of the English Universities]] * 1865 [[China Inland Mission]] * 1865 [[Religious Society of Friends|Friends']] Foreign Mission Association * 1866 [[Delhi Female Medical Mission]] * 1867 [[Friends' Mission in Syria and Palestine]] * 1877 [[Cambridge Mission to Delhi]] * 1880 [[Church of England Zenana Mission|Church of England Zenana Missionary Society]] * 1884 [[Presbyterian Mission to Korea]] * 1892 [[Student Volunteer Movement|Student Volunteer Missionary Union]]
==Missionary societies in the United States and Canada== * 1733 [[Corporation for the Propagation of the Gospel in New England]] * 1787 [[Society for Propagating the Gospel Among the Indians at Boston]] * 1795 [[Religious Society of Friends|Friends']] Missionary Society * 1800 [[New York Missionary Society]] * 1800 [[Connecticut Missionary Society for Indians]] * 1803 [[United States Mission to the Cherokees]] * 1806 [[Western Missionary Society for Indians]] * 1810 [[American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions]] * 1814 [[American Baptist Missionary Union]] (later known as ''American Baptist Foreign Mission Society'' and then American Baptist International Ministries) * 1819 [[American Methodist Episcopal Mission|Methodist Episcopal Church Missionary Society]] * 1826 [[American Home Missionary Society]] * 1832 [[American Baptist Home Mission Society]] * 1833 [[Free-will Baptist Foreign Missionary Society in India]] * 1835 [[Protestant Episcopal Church Mission]] * 1837 [[American Presbyterian Mission|Board of Foreign Missions of the Presbyterian Church (North)]] * 1837 [[Evangelical Lutheran Foreign Missionary Society]] * 1842 [[Seventh Day Baptist Mission|Seventh Day Baptist Missionary Society]] * 1842 [[Strict Baptist Missionary Society]] * 1843 [[Baptist Free Missionary Society]] * 1845 [[American Southern Methodist Episcopal Mission|Methodist Episcopal Church (South)]] * 1845 [[American Southern Baptist Mission|Southern Baptist Convention]] * 1846 [[American Missionary Association]] * 1849 [[American Christian Missionary Society]] * 1857 [[Board of Foreign Missions of (Dutch) Reformed Church]] * 1859 [[Board of Foreign Missions of United Presbyterian Church]] * 1862 [[American Southern Presbyterian Mission|Board of Foreign Missions of the Presbyterian Church (South)]] * 1874 [[Christian Woman's Board of Missions]] * 1876 [[Foreign Christian Missionary Society]] * 1878 [[Evangelical Association Missionary Society]] * 1886 [[Student Volunteer Movement|Student Volunteer Missionary Union]]
==Missionary societies in Australia== * 1892 [[Open Air Campaigners]]
==Missionary societies in Continental Europe== * 1799 [[Rhenish Missionary Society]] * 1815 [[Basel Mission]] * 1859 [[Finnish Missionary Society]] * [[Liebenzell Mission]] {{Expand section|date=June 2008}}
