'''Our Lady of the Wind''', ''Saydet El-Rih'' in Arabic, was built in the Byzantine era in [[Enfeh]], [[Lebanon]].  Even though the roof of the chapel has long collapsed, it still retains traces of wall paintings representing [[Saint George]] and Saint Demetrios, the Omnipotent Christ, two evangelists, some saints and the Virgin calming the wind.<ref>[http://www.lebanon-hotels.com/tourism/ENFCHURCH/ Enfeh churches Lebanon<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It is believed that sailors and fishermen from the village of [[Enfeh]] built the chapel so that the Virgin Mary would protect them as they sailed the [[Mediterranean]].

